  <subfield code="o">1</subfield>
  <subfield code="m">One reason for why gtbin calculates the measurement uncertainty in this way could be that, for a nondetection {C}_{\mathrm{obs}}=0, the Poisson distribution of average {C}_{0}=0 is a δ function, whose dispersion \sigma =0 is unusable. Another reason is that Cobs photons being detected does not imply that the measurement was drawn only from a Poisson distribution of average/peak value Cobs</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="o">2</subfield>
  <subfield code="m">The wind case requires a very weak magnetic field in the forward shock, especially if {\varepsilon }_{e}\gtrsim 0.01, as obtained from modeling the afterglow broadband emission</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="o">3</subfield>
  <subfield code="h">Ackermann et al.</subfield>
  <subfield code="m">(,: #apjaa5891bib5) also concluded that the LAT data offer only weak evidence for a break in the 3-22 s spectrum of 090926, and they found {E}_{\tau }=0.2\,\mathrm{GeV} for a broken power-law fit and {E}_{\tau }=1.4\,\mathrm{GeV} for an exponential cutoff</subfield>
  <subfield code="y">2011</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="o">3</subfield>
  <subfield code="m">using the burst variability timescale {\rm{\Delta }}t=0.15\,{\rm{s}} instead of the peak epoch t\simeq 13\,{\rm{s}}, they inferred a higher Lorentz factor {{\rm{\Gamma }}}_{\tau }=720</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="o">4</subfield>
  <subfield code="m">Not to be confused with the softening of the synchrotron spectrum by {\rm{\Delta }}\beta =1/2 due to electron cooling during one dynamical timescale, which is at a much lower energy than Es</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
  <subfield code="o">5</subfield>
  <subfield code="m">Other mechanisms for a spectral softening—the onset of the Klein-Nishina regime for inverse-Compton scatterings and attenuation by the EBL—should both yield breaks above the LAT range</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">refextract</subfield>
 </datafield>
